## C-01: Add Safety Guards to Journal Matching Threshold
**Priority:** 🔴 P0  
**Sprint:** Week 1 (Mar 10–16)  
**Estimated Hours:** 4h  
**Branch:** `fix/matching-guards`

### Description
The overlap threshold was lowered to 0.40, which risks false-positive matches for short journal names.

### Acceptance Criteria
- [x] Add a **minimum token count guard**: if `max(len(ta), len(tb)) <= 2`, require threshold ≥ 0.70
- [x] Add a `confidence` column to the output CSV: `high` (score ≥ 0.70), `medium` (0.55–0.70), `low` (0.40–0.55)
- [x] Log the top 20 "low confidence" matches to stdout for human review
- [x] Pre-compile all `ABBREV_MAP` regex patterns (currently re-compiled on every call):

```python
# At module level
COMPILED_ABBREV = [(re.compile(pattern, re.IGNORECASE), repl) 
                    for pattern, repl in ABBREV_MAP.items()]

def expand_abbrev(text):
    t = text.lower()
    for pattern, replacement in COMPILED_ABBREV:
        t = pattern.sub(replacement, t)
    return t
```

### Files to Modify
| File | Change |
|---|---|
| [06_match_journals.py](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/etl/06_match_journals.py) | Add guards, confidence column, pre-compile regex |

